      "date": "2019-05-21 15:16:52.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi Minh,\n\nThe build failure is:\n\nliblnetconfig.c:4321:3: error: 'strncpy' output truncated before terminating nul copying as many bytes from a string as its length [-Werror=stringop-truncation]\n\nliblnetconfig.c:722:30: error: '%s' directive output may be truncated writing up to 127 bytes into a region of size 104 [-Werror=format-truncation=]\n\nHowever, the output of configure was:\n\n 00:27:51 checking for -Wno-format-truncation support... yes\n 00:27:51 checking for -Wno-stringop-truncation support... yes\n 00:27:51 checking for -Wno-stringop-overflow support... yes\n\n EXTRA_KCFLAGS: -include /tmp/rpmbuild-lustre-jenkins-xqofKO3Y/BUILD/lustre-2.12.53_46_g8bbaad2/undef.h -include /tmp/rpmbuild-lustre-jenkins-xqofKO3Y/BUILD/lustre-2.12.53_46_g8bbaad2/config.h  -g -I/tmp/rpmbuild-lustre-jenkins-xqofKO3Y/BUILD/lustre-2.12.53_46_g8bbaad2/libcfs/include -I/tmp/rpmbuild-lustre-jenkins-xqofKO3Y/BUILD/lustre-2.12.53_46_g8bbaad2/lnet/include -I/tmp/rpmbuild-lustre-jenkins-xqofKO3Y/BUILD/lustre-2.12.53_46_g8bbaad2/lustre/include -Wno-format-truncation -Wno-stringop-truncation -Wno-stringop-overflow\n\n\"-Wno-format-truncation -Wno-stringop-truncation -Wno-stringop-overflow\" were specified.\n\nDo you know why the above flags were not used while running make?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
